{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id90737315-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4216"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4216"},"text":"§ 4216.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Posting rates of fees","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It shall be the duty of all consular officers at all times to keep posted up in their offices, respectively, in a conspicuous place, and subject to the examination of all persons interested therein, a copy of such rates or tariffs as shall be in force.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id90737316-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(R.S. § 1731.)","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id90737317-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id90737318-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id90737319-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"R.S. § 1731 derived from ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1856-08-18/ch127/s16"},"text":"act Aug. 18, 1856, ch. 127, § 16","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/11/57"},"text":"11 Stat. 57","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was not enacted as part of the Foreign Service Act of 1980 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/u